[ src ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This is where I build packages for the OS.
Usually I just download them directly from AUR or use pacaur.
If you build anything manually feel free to do it here.

[ bin ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Executable NOVIX commands in $PATH


[ common ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Bash logic used throughout NOVIX commands

[ falco ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This is checked out to github.com:falcosecurity/falco-on-arm which is
a hybrid branch I built specifically for NOVIX

Falco should be installed and running by default.
Below are some handy things to do to play with Falco.

   View the logs: 
	sudo journalctl -fu falco

   Start/Stop Falco:
	sudo systemctl start falco
	sudo systemctl stop falco

   Run Falco manually:
	sudo falco

   Falco configuration:
	/etc/falco



[ kubernetes ]
----------------------------------------------------------------------

The directory that holds the Kubernetes lab information and config